---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';

const assessmentAreas = [
	{ title: 'Cognitive Ability', desc: 'Intelligence testing to identify cognitive strengths, weaknesses, and the processing patterns that underlie academic performance.' },
	{ title: 'Academic Achievement', desc: 'Standardized achievement measures in reading, writing, and math to pinpoint specific areas of underperformance.' },
	{ title: 'Processing Skills', desc: 'Working memory, processing speed, and executive functioning — the cognitive engine behind learning.' },
	{ title: 'Aptitude-Achievement Analysis', desc: 'Pattern analysis comparing cognitive ability to academic output to identify specific learning disabilities under DSM-5 criteria.' },
];

const dyslexiaAreas = [
	{ title: 'Phonological Processing', desc: 'The ability to detect, segment, and manipulate the sounds of language — critical for decoding and spelling.' },
	{ title: 'Reading Fluency & Accuracy', desc: 'Timed and untimed measures of word reading, pseudoword decoding, and oral reading fluency.' },
	{ title: 'Reading Comprehension', desc: 'Understanding of connected text at sentence and passage level, including inferential reasoning.' },
	{ title: 'Written Expression', desc: 'Spelling, sentence composition, and the ability to organize and produce written language.' },
];

const referralQuestions = [
	'Why is my child underperforming despite appearing capable?',
	'Does my child have a specific learning disability in reading, writing, or math?',
	'Is my child dyslexic, or is something else affecting their reading?',
	'Are processing speed or working memory weaknesses contributing to academic difficulty?',
	'Are cognitive or psychological factors contributing to learning difficulties?',
	'What accommodations or services would be most effective for school planning?',
];

const facts = [
	{ label: 'Format', value: 'Remote evaluation' },
	{ label: 'Scope', value: 'Cognitive-achievement comparison' },
	{ label: 'Turnaround', value: 'Report within one week' },
	{ label: 'Rate', value: '$1,500 private-pay' },
];
---

<Layout
	title="Learning Disorder & Dyslexia Evaluations | Morning Tide Consulting and Collective"
	description="Remote evaluations for learning disorders and dyslexia — covering cognitive ability, academic achievement, reading fluency, processing skills, and DSM-5 diagnosis. Reports within one week across 40+ PSYPACT states."
>
	<main class="page-main">
		<section class="hero-shell mx-auto max-w-6xl space-y-8">
			<p class="eyebrow">Psychoeducational Evaluations</p>
			<h1 class="max-w-4xl text-5xl leading-none text-(--color-ink) sm:text-6xl">Learning disorder and dyslexia evaluations that find the root cause.</h1>
			<p class="max-w-3xl text-lg leading-8 text-(--color-muted)">
				When a student is struggling, the question is rarely <em>whether</em> there is a problem — the question is <em>what</em> is driving it. These evaluations combine cognitive and achievement testing, processing skill analysis, and aptitude-achievement comparison to deliver a precise learning profile and DSM-5 diagnosis where warranted. When the referral question centers on reading, a dedicated dyslexia battery maps the specific reading profile so families and schools know exactly where to intervene.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section class="mx-auto mt-12 grid max-w-6xl gap-6 lg:grid-cols-2">
			<div class="section-shell rounded-4xl p-8">
				<p class="eyebrow">What We Assess</p>
				<h2 class="mt-4 text-4xl leading-none text-(--color-ink)">Cognitive ability, achievement, and the processing in between.</h2>
				<div class="mt-6 grid gap-4">
					{assessmentAreas.map((area) => (
						<div class="premium-card rounded-3xl p-4">
							<p class="text-sm font-semibold text-(--color-ink)">{area.title}</p>
							<p class="mt-1 text-sm leading-6 text-(--color-muted)">{area.desc}</p>
						</div>
					))}
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="space-y-6">
				<div class="rounded-4xl border border-(--color-line-soft) bg-(--color-surface) p-8 shadow-(--shadow-soft)">
					<p class="eyebrow">Common Referral Questions</p>
					<ul class="mt-6 space-y-3 text-sm leading-7 text-(--color-muted)">
						{referralQuestions.map((item) => (
							<li class="flex gap-3">
								<span class="mt-2 h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-(--color-brand)"></span>
								<span>{item}</span>
							</li>
						))}
					</ul>
				</div>

				<div class="rounded-4xl border border-(--color-line-soft) bg-(--color-surface) p-8 shadow-(--shadow-soft)">
					<p class="eyebrow">At a Glance</p>
					<div class="mt-6 grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">
						{facts.map((fact) => (
							<div class="premium-card rounded-3xl p-5">
								<p class="text-[0.68rem] font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.28em] text-(--color-brand)">{fact.label}</p>
								<p class="mt-3 text-base font-semibold text-(--color-ink)">{fact.value}</p>
							</div>
						))}
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="mx-auto mt-12 max-w-6xl space-y-6">
			<div class="section-shell rounded-4xl p-8 lg:p-10">
				<p class="eyebrow">Dyslexia-Specific Testing</p>
				<h2 class="mt-4 text-4xl leading-none text-(--color-ink)">A detailed look at reading from every angle.</h2>
				<p class="mt-5 max-w-3xl text-base leading-8 text-(--color-muted)">
					When the referral question centers on reading, the evaluation includes a targeted dyslexia battery — measuring phonological processing, fluency, decoding, comprehension, and written expression. The goal is not just to confirm or rule out dyslexia — it is to map the specific reading profile so intervention can be precisely targeted.
				</p>
				<div class="mt-8 grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">
					{dyslexiaAreas.map((area) => (
						<div class="rounded-2xl border border-(--color-line-soft) bg-(--color-surface) p-5">
							<p class="text-sm font-semibold text-(--color-ink)">{area.title}</p>
							<p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-(--color-muted)">{area.desc}</p>
						</div>
					))}
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="mx-auto mt-10 max-w-6xl rounded-4xl border border-(--color-line-soft) bg-(--color-surface) p-8 shadow-(--shadow-soft)">
			<div class="grid gap-8 lg:grid-cols-3">
				<div>
					<p class="eyebrow">Private-Pay Only</p>
					<p class="mt-4 text-base leading-8 text-(--color-muted)">Insurance often limits testing to a narrow set of measures. Private-pay allows a full cognitive-achievement comparison without scope restrictions. HSA/FSA accepted; superbills provided.</p>
				</div>
				<div>
					<p class="eyebrow">School-Ready Report</p>
					<p class="mt-4 text-base leading-8 text-(--color-muted)">Reports include IEP- and 504-compatible recommendations with enough detail for school psychologists, reading specialists, special education teams, and outside providers to act on immediately.</p>
				</div>
				<div>
					<p class="eyebrow">Next Step</p>
					<a class="mt-4 inline-flex rounded-full bg-(--color-accent) px-5 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-(--color-button-ink) shadow-(--shadow-brand)" href="/#contact">Start with an inquiry</a>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>
	</main>
</Layout>
